I used json-server --watch db.json to run the server.
HTML was used to create the structure and CSS was used to style the app.
Data from the JSON file was used to populate different segments while using JavaScript.
I expected some challenges during the coding process like knowing the most suitable way to frame a certain command or writing the command with the right tags.
I had to comment out some sections of code to know what I was doing wrong.
I experienced some blockers and a hard time debugging the code but I got help from online, my TM, and other students.
I added functions like submit to review forms, which enable a user to write a comment on a certain item.
As a user, I can also delete an item that is no longer present.
A buy function has also been added and when clicked it gives the customer a -30 shillings discount on the original price by updating it to a new(-30 ) price.

I believe this idea is great and has potential and I would wish to add more events to it in the near future to enable creators to interact, and add their design pictures and written patterns.

